From 4d803a55e97bb422878de138d96a9c6b00bf8bac Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vignesh U <uvignesh@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Tue, 15 Jul 2025 15:17:20 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 1/5] UPSTREAM: PROTOCOL: wifi: ath12k: Add data structures and
 integration hooks for SP mode TPC

Add support for storing and managing PSD and EIRP power levels required
for 6 GHz Standard Power (SP) AP mode. Without this, configuring transmit
power control (TPC) information is limited due to missing fields in
existing structures.

Introduce new fields in ath12k_reg_tpc_power_info to hold per-channel
PSD and EIRP values, along with counters to track the number of configured
levels. This enables the driver to manage SP-specific power data effectively.

Add a new API stub, ath12k_mac_fill_reg_tpc_info_with_psd_eirp_pwr_for_sp(),
to populate both PSD and EIRP tables. Update ath12k_mac_bss_info_changed()
to select the appropriate TPC fill routine based on the 6 GHz power mode
and firmware capabilities.

Fix incorrect scaling in get_psd_limit(). The AFC PSD response is already
in 0.01 dBm scale and is divided by 100 to convert to dBm/MHz. The function
was further dividing the value by 10, leading to truncation and incorrect
results. Remove the extra division to preserve correct PSD values.

Define the capability flag
WMI_TLV_SERVICE_BOTH_PSD_EIRP_FOR_AP_SP_CLIENT_SP_SUPPORT
to conditionally enable this logic.

Fixes: None
Patch-work: None
Tag: 6G_REGULATORY
Feature: AFC
Patch-dependency:
ath12k/0401-e-UPSTREAM-PROTOCOL-ath12k-implement-6-GHz-minimum-PSD.patch

Signed-off-by: Vignesh U <uvignesh@qti.qualcomm.com>
